::: {.cell hash='functions_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-1_bdbc967b11391e14c418a237595eee03'}

```{.r .cell-code}
compare <- function(x, y) {
  x == y
}
```
:::


We can now use our function:


::: {.cell hash='functions_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-2_1135686de4badb5dc4870027cde22cd9'}

```{.r .cell-code}
compare(2, 3)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] FALSE
```
:::
:::


Note that the result of the last statement is printed automatically:


::: {.cell hash='functions_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-3_df30499d2a76433b36c191969abffb88'}

```{.r .cell-code}
test <- function(x, y) {
  x
  y
}
test(2, 3)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 3
```
:::
:::


If you want to return other results, you need to explicitly use the `print()` function:


::: {.cell hash='functions_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-4_e8f3933e2da38dd55aeb39607923e917'}

```{.r .cell-code}
test <- function(x, y) {
  print(x)
  y
}
test(2, 3)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 2
```
:::

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 3
```
:::
:::
